---
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Delete EdgeEver data" description="How EdgeEver users can delete notes, attachments, local data, and self-hosted accounts.">
  <Container>
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl py-12 text-slate-700 md:py-20">
      <article class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm md:p-10">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-950">Delete EdgeEver data</h1>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 leading-7">
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Delete notes and attachments</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">In the EdgeEver app, move a note to Trash, open Trash, and permanently delete it or empty Trash. Permanently deleting a note also removes its associated attachments from the connected self-hosted instance.</p>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Delete local app data</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Sign out in the app, then clear EdgeEver storage in Android Settings or uninstall the app. This removes the local session, SQLite mirror, drafts, sync queue, and preferences from the device. It does not delete data stored in the self-hosted instance.</p>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Delete an account</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">EdgeEver accounts are created and controlled by the administrator of the self-hosted instance, not by the mobile app developer. Ask that administrator to delete the account and any server-side data that must also be removed. If you operate the instance yourself, use its user-management controls or delete the associated Cloudflare D1 and R2 data.</p>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Get help</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">For questions about the deletion process, open an issue in the <a class="text-teal-700 underline" href="https://github.com/tianma-if/edgeever/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">EdgeEver GitHub repository</a>. Do not include passwords, API tokens, or private note content.</p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>
  </Container>
</Layout>
